 options**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out the current native-image options. It seems there might be an issue since WLRmic initializes at build time, even though `--initialize-at-run-time` is only active for nativeTestCompile. I wonder if the dynamic report is generated by the JVM. I'm also considering if the dynamic coverage from javaTest with the agent is involved. It's interesting that the coverage report shows WLRmic's getMethod/invoke being covered—could that be due to JVM tests with the Native Image agent tracking?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VAeFNhYpgiFBwzoiTUD2MYrh|fc_0cb53d46c71cf5d30169f00656cba88191b11d88a66ddb463b", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/WLRmicTest.java", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2065, "output": 1570, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35891, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777337917326, "responseId": "resp_0cb53d46c71cf5d30169f0063dd78881918333a87a5b71fa66"}}
