[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring test package options**\n\nI'm considering whether to add a test helper in the same package. The rule says to keep tests outside library packages, but the helper isn’t a top-level test. We previously added a weblogic package helper. If I add a non-test helper in org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.rmic, it might access package-private static methods. It's against the spirit of keeping tests separate. I’m also contemplating using Ant's `Project` to run the `<rmic compiler=\"weblogic\">`, which seems more aligned with the public API, but I'll need to check the report after the next attempt.\n\n**Assessing native-image options**\n\nI'm trying to figure out the current native-image options. It seems there might be an issue since WLRmic initializes at build time, even though `--initialize-at-run-time` is only active for nativeTestCompile. I wonder if the dynamic report is generated by the JVM. I'm also considering if the dynamic coverage from javaTest with the agent is involved. It's interesting that the coverage report shows WLRmic's getMethod/invoke being covered—could that be due to JVM tests with the Native Image agent tracking?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cb53d46c71cf5d30169f0063f80148191818904d8c71fb824\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8AZWHfkdGJeJlgfhe6VKuJ0cIiOOG--Fsi5_CQGp0BxeknIlrwlajEaZ3y0Hsn-HMgkV2pQLZim6Eu0h_TsP19h0cISRt-exwP21nA-1faeWMoLO_2yE5liS-ZtOTLIKs8kb3fvAWS2K10PcNQC9P0ukZm9XD-_Zy3H3yfuGHQcoLYysi0YFYzyKKdtpMlkPXZtlVkg2FSqYexv5xndaP22qICUE0WAAtusdGhbSqz5Kf4tqcPn_U8m8ey2Xcoj4jtEpaG9t0lAyEg8WZKT_Ojirv0E2MIcQktLChnw8_t2cbTcDDQSykYpbPBxsWvt2kPXwxMt_d7pIhw-nSA5eTcRi58SLMd9Sg_kldOMOoC8GL9jIoSL7VLSZRwmwRCAXCAMx3DtmCOb-1WXzwaz_RjMpCYbAZMeku6t5zYPUO-O8cg7NWd17BbIaCEXCp23AJ1sgOpQoGrVyo4KzWSg2fx9BPcweI7IT9HR0uzl-tU9ghhtK9DSeATaG0vigCgroxjPE1XZ7nsH1eoOOOJIEpFKGDYUGdypYe1ZR10yodx1HMzXpYoavOxpVAyXKPjcGF7xDQq_3Cn5YIaxPK10xM